  "prompt": "Where can I get a place to stay in goa for a low budget?",
  "response": "Finding budget accommodation in Goa is easier than ever, as the region offers a range of options that cater to various budgets. Here are some suggestions for finding low-cost places to stay in Goa:\n\n1. **Guesthouses and Homestays**: These often provide affordable rates and a more personal touch. You can find these through websites like Airbnb, Tripadvisor, or Homestays.com.\n\n2. **Hostels**: Popular among backpackers, hostels offer shared dormitory rooms at low prices. Websites like Hostelworld, Booking.com, and Hostelbookers can help you find hostels in Goa.\n\n3. **Budget Hotels**: Many budget hotels offer decent amenities at affordable prices. Websites like Oyo Rooms, MakeMyTrip, and Goibibo can help you find budget hotel options in Goa.\n\n4. **Agoda**: This website specializes in budget accommodation and might have good deals on places to stay in Goa that fit your budget.\n\n5. **Beach Huts and Cabins**: These are basic structures located near the beaches, offering a unique experience. Look for beach huts in areas like Palolem, Agonda, and Anjuna beaches.\n\n6. **Local Listings**: Sometimes, walking around and asking locals can lead to finding very affordable stays that might not be listed online.\n\nAreas to consider for budget stays include Anjuna, Vagator, Palolem, Agonda, and Baga, as they have a good mix of budget accommodation options.\n\nRemember to book in advance if you're visiting during peak season (November to February), as prices tend to be higher and availability limited.",
